This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Programmes are efficiently designed, coordinated, managed and supported to meet quality programming standards in achieving results for children in development and humanitarian settings.

description.narrative: UNICEF Pacific massively increased its voice, reach, and engagement with key advocacy targets through advocacy campaigns and activities aligned with country, global and regional strategies. On digital platforms, UNICEF Pacific recorded a reach of 35m, with 1.7m engagement, 2.2m impressions on Twitter, and over 140,000 reach on Instagram. Additionally, UNICEF Pacific recorded over 500 media hits in the Pacific region and 300 global media hits. Advocacy plans were also linked to COVID-19 across 14 Pacific Islands Countries and Territories (PICTs). Increased donor visibility was provided through new partnerships, including COVAX and COVID-19 responses, with new donor plans and partnerships developed. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/02/2022
